service.name: Assessment Subsidy for Overseas Trained Professionals Programme
service.description: Assessment Subsidy for Overseas Trained Professionals Programme (ASDOT) is to enable eligible overseas trained Australian residents to obtain recognition of their qualifications for the purposes of registration and/or employment in Australia. The programme provides grants for approved assessments and/or examinations that are necessary to qualify for employment in Australia, by professions that are self-regulated by law.
